author: rhuijben
msg: Since it is now easy to calculate the absolute path from a diff handler, we
can just use that in the deprecated wrapper instead of the stupid
'local_dir_abspath' argument hack I added earlier in 1.7 development
(Whether it is hashed in DB will provide the necessary check on whether
the directory is available locally. And because we are providing a diff, this
is exactly the information we need here)
wrap_4to3_file_deleted): Calculate directory path and just check if we have
wrap_4to3_dir_closed): Check if we have an access baton for the directory
